<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-13T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1023: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-13T17:00:00-07:00">December 13, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>102. The political situation has now improved considerably and the new
                            Government seems to have complete control of the situation. At the
                            present there does not seem to be danger of any outbreak or unrest in
                            the immediate future.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McCafferty</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>